    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="451"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 351.117/17.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Herrick</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>231. Your 206 [207], October 27. Chandeysson given certificate of citizenship
                    about August 12; was also assisted to obtain funds; now enrolled in 7th Company,
                    120th Territorial Regiment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
